<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6210b358-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s43"><num value="43">§ 43.</num><heading> Persons paid for other services not paid for interpreting</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No person employed by the United States and paid for any other service shall be paid for interpreting.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6210b359-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1910-04-04/ch140/s2">Apr. 4, 1910, ch. 140, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/272">36 Stat. 272</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
